    xml:id="pie-peach" >
    <title>Super Simple &amp; Yummy Peach Pie</title>
    <para><emphasis role="italic">a recipe from 
        Ren&#x00E9;e Rendon</emphasis></para>
    <note>
        <para><emphasis role="italic">
            This is my favorite pie recipe. 
            It is super fast and easy to throw together and tastes soooo yummy!
        </emphasis>
        </para>
    </note>
<para>
    <emphasis role="bold">Ingredients:</emphasis>
        <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para>pastry for a double-crust 9-inch pie</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>5 cups frozen peaches</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>1 cup sugar</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>1/3 - 1/2 cup flour</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>1/4 - 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon
                    </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>2 tablespoons butter</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>2 tablespoons sugar (for top of pie)</para>
            </listitem>
        </itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>
   <emphasis role="bold">Directions:</emphasis>
    <orderedlist>
        <listitem>
            <para>Preheat oven to 425 degrees F.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Stir together flour, 1 cup sugar, and cinnamon and set aside.
            </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Microwave peaches until thawed.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Mix together peaches with the combined dry ingredients.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Turn into pastry-lined pie pan and dot with butter.
            </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Cover with top crust, cut slits in it, seal the edges.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Sprinkle top with 2 tablespoons of sugar.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Cover the edges with foil to prevent over browning.
            </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Bake 35 to 45 minutes or until crust is brown 
                and juice begins to bubble through the slits 
                in the crust.
            </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Pie may be frozen for future use.</para>
        </listitem>
    </orderedlist>
</para>
    <warning>
<para>
    Put a cookie sheet under the pie when baking, 
    so the juices donâ€™t overflow and burn on the oven floor.
</para>
    </warning>
